From Mark Shneyder Subject Re Radio stations Add Boston's WEEI as the Bruins' flagship You probably won't pick it up anywhere outside of Boston since it's only a watt The Bruins also have network stations in all New England This could be the Bruins' last year on 'EEI which also happens to be an all sports radio The problem is that the Bruins are not too happy being moved over to a different station WMEX whenever there is a the same night conflict with the NBA's Boston This happened times during the course of the regular The Celtics own financially troubled WEEI The Bruins might resurface on WHDH next Stay PPV Mark